Great summary — and I appreciate the candor. It's always refreshing to see someone acknowledge the quirks of the tool rather than pretending it's flawless.

You might also want to consider the `Result` and `Option` types when working with external APIs — they can be a bit of a "gotcha" for folks coming from more lenient languages. But that's probably a matter of style more than design.

Also, while `Vec` is indeed the go-to in most cases, there are still a few niche scenarios where `LinkedList` shines (though I'm not sure I've ever encountered one in the wild). But I suppose that's the price of having options.

Keep up the good work — and maybe consider